Doesn&#x27;t UBER also:<p>1.  Finance cars for their drivers;
2.  Provide the legal interpretation of federal/state/county/local laws and regulations to its drivers;
3.  Provide the actual tools (except the car) to complete the work;
4.  Provide training for drivers;
5.  Pay bonuses to drive specific hours and/or in specific locations/jurisdictions<p>All things that most companies can&#x27;t do with independent contractors?
